text: Imre Petneházy was a Hungarian épée fencer and modern pentathlete from Serbia. Imre competed at the 1932 Summer Olympics. He was born on April 13, 1905 and died on September 23, 1972.Imre Petneházy == References == Category:1905 births Category:1972 deaths Category:Hungarian fencers Category:Hungarian modern pentathletes Category:Olympians for Hungary
